Program: Outlook
Title: 13/03/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00pcj8p
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 14 Mar 2012
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, the 87-year-old Swiss man who was removed from his family by the government and put to work on a farm. Like tens of thousands of other children, Arthur Honegger became a 'contract child'. He tells Lucy Ash about those lost years and why he is speaking out about his stolen childhood. Also the Liberian doctor tackling prejudice against Aids by writing a book about her gay brother. And we cross the Pacific to meet the cowboys of Hawaii. Show less